rComments: He does a really good job conveying class material. Labs, 2 midterms and a final. Labs are easy. There's a lot of content and it's heavy on the science side, but you'll definitely be fine if you're in the BSc stream. I think he's kind of funny too, so I'm happy to listen to the lectures.

Love Charles. Anatomy/biology has always been my weak spot, but he made it tolerable, even interesting. Everything's posted at beginning of semester, and you just need to pace yourself. He's very knowledgeable and willing to help you understand the material.

Dr. Collin is a fantastic professor. He is very knowledgeable and clearly loves what he is teaching. His lectures are engaging, even when they are online and you can't even see him. He is easy to reach out to and is very responsive. One midterm, one final and four labs (easy 100% on labs if you follow basic instructions).

Very interesting class and knowledgeable professor. Taught course hands-off but taught exceptionally well. Material was easy to understand and very visible. Explained things clearly with examples. Gave extra math help which was appreciated. No readings - only lectures, 5 labs, midterm, and final. Enjoyable and easy course.

Professor Collin is a really great professor. 3108 is a challenging course because it is a combination of psychology, math, anatomy, and methods. There is a lot of material. But, the expectations are very clear and the exams are fair. He is an engaging speaker who cares about the material and students. Funny jokes. Recommend the text for labs.

Hard class content, can't lie, but Prof. Collin makes it extremely interesting and not difficult to succeed. I don't come from a science background and still found myself understanding and interested. He really knows his stuff and the grading criteria is extremely fair. Would recommend this class with him, so interesting.

Great prof and super interesting material, but extremely difficult exams. Labs were fairly easy, but the tests are made up of 35% math, 35% anatomy, and 30% MC. Not laid out like the average PSY course. If you prepare for the math and anatomy, you'll do fine, but even the MC was much harder than average. By far the most challenging course I've had.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Course covers a lot of information (similar to BIO courses w/regards to sensory physiology). Despite the volume of material, Prof Collins makes it interesting and easy to understand. He is a very caring Prof - gets to know students' names and offers to help with graduate/career/life advice. His exams are also hilarious!

He's a very nice prof who clearly care about his students. Do not take this course if you're not proficient in physics. PSY course sequence doesn't prepare you at all for what's thought, luckily Charles and the TAs are really great at explaining concepts and providing feedback.
Very well spoken. Charles is clearly an expert in this subject. it's very science based so a decent amount of memorisation including some psychophysics but I feel like I'm really learning from him.

Professor Collin was great! I was initially worried about taking Perception, but he is a great lecturer and kind/caring. The labs with the TA were very cool and not hard at all which was a relief. A lot of material however, really does require constant reviewing. Midterm and Final has MC, diagrams and math, MC was difficult but the others not bad.

One of the best profs in the psychology department. The course has a lot of material, but the labs are helpful and he lectures well. The class is fun and the exams are hilarious and a pleasure to write. He is always willing to help and sends out helpful emails (scholarships, opportunities, etc.).

I loved this class! For a psych class it contained aspects of math, bio, philosophy and neuroscience which I found really refreshing. Charles is super knowledgeable and really cares about every student! Pros: the labs are super easy and will boost your grade Cons: there is a ton of material to learn and a bit of math (very easy math)

I absolutely loved this class! For a psych class it was a refreshing mix of biology, neuroscience, math, philosophy, etc. It changed the way I think about the world around me! Charles is amazing and he really cares about each student. Pros: the labs are super easy and will help boost your grade Cons: there is math (but it is super easy)

Going into this course I was kind of afraid I would do poorly but Prof. Collin is very organized and teaches really well. It is obvious that he has been teaching this course for a very long time which is reassuring. Textbook is required for labs but that's it. Exams are fair, I always did better than I thought. Somehow finished with and A!

Sciencey course (hardest of the three that you have to pick from: cognition, learning/conditioning). AMESOME PROF. You do NOT need the textbook, study the slides. There are a lot of them, but he makes it SO easy to do well, and is AMAZING at explaining concepts. Accessible outside of lectures, super engaging. I'm a BA and this was a mark booster
Great guy. There is a ton of info in the perception course you need to know, but he makes the lectures fun and interesting. Genuinely cares about your success.

Charles is an incredibly gifted lecturer- he makes complex ideas simple, and provides useful mnemonics for memory-heavy parts. He themes his exams on fictional universes (this years midterm was the Marvel extended universe). Plus, he makes an effort to learn everyone's names, which is a nice little touch.
Dr. Collin is amazing and his lectures and exams are funny. Start reading early cos it's A LOT of material to get done.

He's a nice guy and a very clear lecturer, if you understand in class then there isn't much need for notes. If your struggling take notes on that section. Take down answers to the questions he has on his slides. His exams are tough only because there is so much material in the course. Exams: 1/3 math, 1/3 drawing and labeling diagrams, 1/3 MC(hard)

Professor Collin is a great prof, his classes are usually really interesting and he's always willing to help out! He's definitely not an easy prof though and I did find there be an extensive amount of material to remember especially for the cumulative final. If you're willing to memorize you'll be fine

Amazing lecturer, keeps content interesting. Midterm was 30 MC, 2 diagrams, and 5 math questions. Exam was 60 MC, 3 diagrams, and 7 math questions. Tests were kinda tricky but thats to be expected with the amount of information in the course. Labs were really easy if you answered straight from the slides. Take it if you're good at memorizing.

He is funny and can make boring material better for the most part. Only need the textbook to re-read what his lectures say. The labs are pretty easy but time consuming and can be a bit ambiguous sometimes. They don't give feedback for the labs unless you ask. The final is cumulative but if you work hard its not too bad for a science course

He is a great prof and really funny! He makes the boring material better. If you attend class and pay attention you won't need the textbook because he only tests on what's in his slides. The labs aren't hard but can be very ambiguous and time consuming. Tests aren't easy but they aren't extremely hard if you study.

Avoid taking perception with Charles. Although he is a compassionate individual, he expects far too much considering most students are taking 5 coursessemester. Stats is not a prereq yet 13 of the exams comprise math questions. Unnecessary. Immense amount of material and the weekly labs are quite time consuming. Many students failed the midterm.

Good prof. Went through a lot of demonstrations in class of the different things we were studying (like optical/aural illusions). Fairly interesting class. The labs are easy marks. The exams aren't easy but should be fine if you study, and there are no papers.

Had for perception. Fantastic prof; one of my favourites. Very clear, provides great demonstrations in class, funny, fair tests, great communication (incl. email), interesting extra info added.  Very personal...learns everyone's names :)
I looooooooove Professor Collin. He is so hot and awesome, I wish I could take every class with him. <3

A little bit demanding but this prof knows what he is talking about. His lectures are clear and he's always more than willing to meet outside of class. He also has regular "question periods" in his lectures to make sure everyone is following along!

Midterm was unnecessarily hard, his sketch and label questions require you to actually draw and then label, no diagrams are provided. Nice prof but he was quite monotone and it made it hard to listen attentively in class. Final is cumulative and the labs require a lot of work and are detail oriented.

Very clear and always available to help you. If you email him he will email back the same day.The labs weren't hard and helped boost your mark. A lot of memorization. Definitely go to class if you want to get a good mark. Final exam is cumulative. Great prof!

One of my favourite profs. He is very nice, sincere, & caring. The labs are worth 35% of your mark, guaranteed at least 90% in this section. Key to the exams = KNOW THE DIAGRAMS! He knows his students' on a first name basis and makes you feel at ease when learning about neuroscience-like concepts. Course content is essential for the psych GRE test!

IF YOU ARE PLANNING ON TAKING PERCEPTION, DONT TAKE IT WITH COLLIN, I M STUDYING FOR THE FINAL RIGHT NOW AND I JUST REALIZED HOW MUCH STUFF WE HAVE TO KNOW SINCE IT IS COMPREHENSIVE.... I HATE IT! THE CONTENT OF THIS COURSE IS REALLY HEAVY COMPARE TO MY OTHER COURSES

Collin is very friendly, very helpful prof. Made the content of this course understandable. He will always meet you outside his office hours if you need help! Exams are fair, to get a good grade you have to give yourself plently of time to study for the midterm and final because there is a lot of content! Great prof though!
He's too inflexible.
The midterm is easy. Focus on the notes. Dr. Collin is a solid prof. I highly recommend his class.

I did not find professor Collins to be wonderful, he was very monotonous,he made the material harder than it is; and quite frankly, it was hard to sit through his very boring lectures. Also, I found he played down the midterm saying it would be very easy, when in fact he made it quite difficult when it did not need to be.
WONDERFUL!!! He is a brilliant man who knows his stuff. Actually makes this class interesting. Midterm and paper was fair. VERY helpful and actually cares enough to help you out.

Methodical, clear and answers questions (no matter how difficult or simplistic or stupid). Very good prof, and approachable; very logical. Addicted to coffee. I hope one day he will teach stats; the school needs him!!!
-material is well represented on exams. Lecture slides are thoroughly explained. Good cover of material in labs.
He is super. Sharp dude too. You can tell he knows his stuff and he genuinely cares about his students.
He is excellent, just great. This class is NOT overly hard at all. Prof Collins is a genuine and knowledgeable prof.

I'm the guy who asks a stupid million questions :) -- It's a dry subject, but Prof. Collins is a really good teacher and he makes the subject as interesting as it can be, and he really appreciates feedback from his students and is always willing to hear them out and meet them whenever.

The class is hard,, dry and boring.  I don't know how he is usually, but in our class we have one guy who asks a million stupid questions a minute.  As a teacher though he's good and extremely helpful outside of class.

Prof C is the best!! Sooo smart and really makes research methods interesting!! Can't go wrong with this prof, wants you to do well and will work with you to help. Responds to emails very quickly.  Walked away with a good mark and a smile, for research methods that isn't too bad!!

if you have to take research methods, take it with him. he's a good prof, he's just teaching a boring class. he tries to make it fun though. the labs are a lot of work for 5% but they really help for the exam. he answers questions by email almost instantly! props to him.
I don't understand why he's gotten such good reviews. The class is unbelievably boring, but should be easy -- only he makes it *hard*. Why, Just to be obnoxious?

I really like Prof Collins, although he teaches a dull class he tries to make it interesting and does add his own wit.  Someone writes that he uses nerd wit..but what they don't know is..they will soon be there if they had only half the intelligence he does...He is an excellent prof.

Seems nice. Course material *very* dry, and he often speaks monotonously. Tried to lighten up the material with occasional nerd-wit. Lectures expand on textbook, but are sooo boring. He provides class slides online. If experimental psych is your thing, you'll like him.
Really nice guy, funny, kind of jolly.  Sometimes he is hard to understand, but he's smart.  On occasion I would have to fight falling asleep, but that was my fault.  I'd recommend him.
Very helpful.  Boring course material.  Love the beard!
